1. Making a basic short range creative cannon.

Difficulty: 2/10
Files edited: Client.java

Step 1: Adding Animations

Open client.java and find

[code]public int GetWepAnim(int id)[/code]

Under one of the }'s add..

[code]if(id == 6082) // cannon
{
return 1084;
}[/code]

This is basically just setting the emote every time you attack with the weapon.

Next scroll down till you see
[code]public int GetRunAnim(int id)[/code]

Then under the } add this
[code]if(id == 6082) // cannon
{
return 2318;
}[/code]

This is basically doing the same thing but just the animation while running

Once more, scroll down till you see

[code]public int GetWalkAnim(int id)[/code]

Under one of the }'s add this

[code]if(id == 6082) // cannon
{
return 2318;
}[/code]

Doing the same thing as the last two but with the walking animation


Now for the last time scroll down until you see

[code]public int GetStandAnim(int id)[/code]

Under } add..

[code]if(id == 6082) // cannon
{
return 2316;
}[/code]

What we just did: Made animations for walking, standing, running, and attacking.

Step 2: Getting our cannon to make sound (Credits too Wolf)

Search up

[code]public void frame61[/code]

Under the last } add this

[code]public void frame174(int i1, int i2, int i3)//This allows you to play sounds
{
outStream.createFrame(174);
outStream.writeWord(i1); // sound being played
outStream.writeByte(i2); // time after (leave at 000)
outStream.writeWord(i3); // time sound lasts
//sM("Frame 174 tested");
updateRequired = true;
appearanceUpdateRequired = true;
}
[/code]

Good were done we basically just added the method to make sounds

Step 3: Making the cannon have a gfx and do damage

Search this is client.java:

[code]if(UseCrossBow && misc.random(5)==1 && playerEquipment[playerArrows] == 881){[/code]

Under the last } put this

[code]setAnimation(GetWepAnim(playerEquipment[playerWeapon]));
if(playerEquipment[playerWeapon] == 6082){ // weaponid
hitDiff = misc.random(40); // how powerful it is
stillgfx(287, EnemyY, EnemyX); // gfx
frame174(233, 000, 030); // sound
actionInterval = getbattleTimer(); // battletimer
lastAction = System.currentTimeMillis(); // action
}[/code]

What this code above basically does is if you attack an npc or player with the weapon the hit difference will be 40 (the actual hit is based on opponent's defence), an explosion will happen, and a explosive sound will happen every time you fire the weapon.

Then were done! Save and compile. I will NOT tell you how to make the cannon long range.

2. Using the droppedItem method

Difficulty 1/10
Files edited: Client.java


Open Client.java and search up

[code]public void dropItem(int droppedItem, int slot) {[/code] 

Scroll down and you should see something like this

[code]    if (playerRights == 2) {
      sM("Dropping has been disabled, use ::empty to delete your inventoy instead.");
      return ;
    }[/code]

If you wanted to make a certain item Undroppable you would put something like this under one of the }'s

[code]    if (droppedItem == ####) {
      sM("You Cant drop this");
      return ;
    }[/code]

#### = itemid

The code is basically saying that if you try and drop the item id specified it will send you the message "You can't drop this" and it won't drop, it will just stay in your inventory.

If you wanted to make it so when you drop an item it triggers an effect you would put something like this

[code]if(droppedItem == 3006 && !isInJail()){ //itemid, and won't happen if in jail
deleteItem(3006, 1); // deleting the item out of inventory
dealDamage(10); // deals 10 dmg (based on defence)
hitDiff = 10; // deals 10 dmg (based on defence)	
plrText = "Wow.. What a freaking Show!!! But that hurt.."; // player text
plrTextUpdateRequired = true; // updates the text
updateRequired = true; // updates the screen
hitUpdateRequired = true; // updates the hit
setAnimation(2968); // sets emote
stillgfx(287, absY + 1, absX); // graphics
stillgfx(287, absY - 1, absX); // graphics
stillgfx(287, absY, absX - 1); // graphics
stillgfx(287, absY, absX + 1); // graphics
stillgfx(446, absY - 1, absX - 1); // graphics
stillgfx(446, absY - 1, absX + 1); // graphics
stillgfx(446, absY + 1, absX + 1); // graphics
stillgfx(446, absY + 1, absX - 1); // graphics
stillgfx(582, absY + 2, absX);  // graphics
stillgfx(582, absY - 2, absX); // graphics
stillgfx(582, absY, absX - 2); // graphics
stillgfx(582, absY, absX + 2); // graphics
frame174(233, 000, 500); // sound
return;
}[/code]

This code is basically saying that if you item id 3006 is dropped and the person isn't in jail, instead of the item actually dropping it will delete out of your inventory, you will take 10 damage, your player will actually say the text "Wow.. What a freaking Show!!! But that hurt..", it swill set an emote for throwing something, explosions will appear everywhere around you and there will be an explosion sound.

3. Using the itemOnObject Method

Difficulty 1/10
Files Edited: Client.java

This is partly the same thing as the above, just with using item on objects triggers an effect.

Part 1/1: Find the case and using it correctly

Search up the code below in client.java

[code]case 192:[/code]

You should see something like

[code]		case 192:
			// Use an item on object
			junk = inStream.readSignedWordBigEndianA();
			int UsedOnObjectID = inStream.readUnsignedWordBigEndian();
			int UsedOnY = inStream.readSignedWordBigEndianA();
			int ItemSlot = (inStream.readSignedWordBigEndianA() - 128);
			int UsedOnX = inStream.readUnsignedWordBigEndianA();
			int ItemID = inStream.readUnsignedWord();
			if (!playerHasItem(ItemID))
				break;[/code]

scroll down a bit more and you should now see..

[code]if(UsedOnObjectID == 10638){
if(ItemID == 526){
deleteItem(526, 1);
addSkillXP(40*getLevelForXP(playerXP[5]), 5);
sM("You receive some prayer experience.");
setAnimation(894);
lowGFX(247,0);
}
if(ItemID == 532){
deleteItem(532, 1);
addSkillXP(80*getLevelForXP(playerXP[5]), 5);
sM("You receive some prayer experience.");
setAnimation(894);
lowGFX(247,0);
}[/code]

Pretty self explanitory now? But for thos 0.001% that get NOTHING here is a little breakdown

If you wanted an itemid to be used on an object and you wanted got an item it would look something like this

[code]if(UsedOnObjectID == #### && ItemID == ****){ // item id used on object
deleteItem(****, %); // deletes item
addItem(&&&&, %); // adds item
}[/code]

#### = object id you want to be used on by item
**** = item id you want to use with the object
% = amount
&&&& = item you want to be added to inventory

if you want to make it add an item use 

[code]addItem(itemid, amount);[/code]

Delete an item

[code]deleteItem(itemid, amount);[/code]

Have graphics like fire, explosions, etc.

[code]stillgfx(graphic id, absY, absX);[/code]

Use an emote

[code]setAnimation(emote id)[/code]

etc.etc.

4. Making an object/item give you random item/items.

PLEASE MAKE SURE YOU OPEN ITEM.JAVA AND NOT! ITEM.CFG!!!

Files edited: Item.java, Client.java (if using object), potions.java (if using item).

Step 1: Choosing the random items to give.

Open Item.java and search 

[code]random[/code]

You should see something like this

[code]   public static int Barrows[] = {4734,4710,4724,4726,4728,4730,4718,4718,4732,4736,4738,4716,4720,4722,4753,4747,4755,4757,4759,4708,4712,4714,4745,4749,4751,7462,7462,7462,7462,7462,7462,7462,7462,7462,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592,592};
[/code]

Under one of the }'s add...

[code]    public static int Box[] = {itemid,itemid,itemid,itemid,itemid... (go as long as you want.)};

        public static int randomBox()
        {
            return Box[(int)(Math.random()*Box.length)];
        }[/code]

it's perfectly fine to put an item id more then once. It controls the chances of getting which item.

Step 2: Choosing the object to give item (If you want an item to give random stuff go to next part.)

Open Client.java and search

[code]if(objectID == 10284){[/code]

under the } add.

[code]
if(objectID == ####){
addItem(Item.randomBox(), 1);
sM("You take a random item from the object");
}[/code]

#### = object id

This is basically just saying if you click the specified object id it will add any random item that you put in item.java, and send you the message "You take a random item from the object".

If you wanted to make it admin + change it to this

[code]if(objectID == ####)  && playerRights >= @){
addItem(Item.randomBox(), 1);
sM("You take a random item from the object");
}[/code]

#### = object id
@ = player rights (0 normal player, 1 mod, 2 admin, 3 owner, 4 hidden admin)

This is basically just saying if you click the specified object id and your player rights is higher than the one you put it will add any random item that you put in item.java, and send you the message "You take a random item from the object"

If you wanted it to add more then 1 random item you would just add another

[code]addItem(Item.randomBox(), 1);[/code]

 with the one thats there.

Step 3: Making the item give you a random item (If you did the last part just skip too end)

Open potions.java and right away you should see

[code]import java.io.*;

public class potions {
	public void buryItem(int item, int slot, int ID) {
		boolean used = true;
		client c = (client) server.playerHandler.players[ID];
		if (item != c.playerItems[slot] - 1){
			return;
		}
		if (c.playerHasItem(item)) {
			switch (item) {
			case 5509:
				c.fillSmallPouch();
				break;
			case 5510:
				c.fillMediumPouch();
				break;
			case 5512:
				c.fillLargePouch();
				break;
			case 5514:
				c.fillGiantPouch();
				break;[/code]

Under one of the "break;" add.

[code]			case ####:
				c.addItem(Item.randomBox(), 1);
				break;[/code]

#### = itemid

This is basically just saying if you click the specified item id it will add any random item that you put in item.java.

And if you want it to add more then 1 random item just add another

[code]addItem(Item.randomBox(), 1);[/code]

 with the one there.

And were done!

Save compile and test these tutorials

